hopobject.body: Is there ? oxcarbazepine side effects drugs.com Macdonald’s direction is alert to every nuance in the group-dynamic but then he’s got a crack cast, with Toby Jones particularly wonderful as the rumpled Schultz, all effortful smiles and hands-in-pockets un-ease, Fenella Woolgar sweetly brittle as the floundering thespian Theresa and Imelda Staunton little short of magnificent as the determinedly encouraging Marty, withholding so much behind her kindly, watchful gaze. We may not be American. We may never have ended up on the wooden-floor of a hall in some out-of-the-way place like this, reaching after some ill-defined moment of personal transformation, but one way or another, yes, we’ve all been here.
